1
00:00:10,333 --> 00:00:17,200
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:32,500
[MARLA] According to
an anonymous philosopher,

3
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:35,300
<i>love can be best explained
through Science.</i>

4
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:39,067
<i>You see,
science has many branches.</i>

5
00:00:39,367 --> 00:00:41,433
<i>It has many things to discover,</i>

6
00:00:41,433 --> 00:00:42,600
<i> to analyze,</i>

7
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:43,467
<i> to solve,</i>

8
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:45,567
<i> just like love.</i>

9
00:00:45,567 --> 00:00:52,500
[UPBEAT MUSIC CONTINUES]

10
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:00,233
[DAPHNE] Marla!

11
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:02,433
This is so bad!

12
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:04,233
Have you seen it?

13
00:01:04,233 --> 00:01:05,300
What’s happening?

14
00:01:05,300 --> 00:01:06,467
[NYX] No!

15
00:01:06,467 --> 00:01:07,467
<i> No!</i>

16
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:08,567
<i> No!</i>

17
00:01:08,567 --> 00:01:09,833
[NYX CRYING]

18
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:11,367
<i> No...</i>

19
00:01:13,333 --> 00:01:14,533
- No!
- [MARLA] Nyx?!

20
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:17,067
Nyx, what happened?

21
00:01:17,467 --> 00:01:18,433
What’s wrong?

22
00:01:18,433 --> 00:01:19,800
No... no!

23
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:20,733
Why?

24
00:01:21,300 --> 00:01:25,767
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

25
00:01:25,767 --> 00:01:26,833
[MARLA] In science

26
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:28,667
<i>there's a lot of uncertainties,</i>

27
00:01:28,667 --> 00:01:30,467
<i> a lot of possible answers,</i>

28
00:01:30,467 --> 00:01:32,033
<i> possible results.</i>

29
00:01:32,467 --> 00:01:33,833
<i> And sometimes,</i>

30
00:01:33,833 --> 00:01:36,333
<i>these results are
not what you wanted</i>

31
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:37,700
<i> or what you expect.</i>

32
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:44,700
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

33
00:01:57,100 --> 00:01:59,167
<i>Even if you follow
the right procedure,</i>

34
00:01:59,167 --> 00:02:00,200
<i> or right equation,</i>

35
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,367
<i> or formula...</i>

36
00:02:01,367 --> 00:02:04,600
<i>it doesn’t guarantee you
the right conclusion.</i>

37
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:09,367
[SCREAMS] Aah!

38
00:02:09,367 --> 00:02:14,633
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

39
00:02:14,667 --> 00:02:17,667
[MURMURING]

40
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:31,367
[NYX] No!

41
00:02:31,367 --> 00:02:38,333
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

42
00:02:38,333 --> 00:02:41,633
[MURMURING]

43
00:02:53,500 --> 00:03:00,433
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

44
00:03:01,767 --> 00:03:06,833
[MURMURING]

45
00:03:08,733 --> 00:03:09,833
[MARLA] What’s worse is that

46
00:03:09,833 --> 00:03:12,500
<i>one failure can lead
to different scenarios,</i>

47
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:15,500
<i>different theories that make
science more complicated</i>

48
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:16,900
<i> than it already is.</i>

49
00:03:17,867 --> 00:03:19,167
[WARREN] Excuse me.

50
00:03:19,167 --> 00:03:25,900
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

51
00:03:27,533 --> 00:03:28,667
Marla, are you okay?

52
00:03:28,667 --> 00:03:31,200
- Stop looking--
- No! Get away!

53
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:33,900
[SOBBING]

54
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:35,233
[WARREN] Turn off the screens!

55
00:03:35,467 --> 00:03:36,500
Get out of my way!

56
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:47,767
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

57
00:04:03,367 --> 00:04:05,433
[MARLA] But here’s the thing
about love...

58
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:08,733
<i>Sure, we can compare it
to science.</i>

59
00:04:09,467 --> 00:04:12,833
<i>But can we explain it
in its simplest form?</i>

60
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:14,500
<i> I highly doubt that.</i>

61
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:21,467
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

62
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:42,867
<i> When an experiment fails</i>

63
00:04:42,867 --> 00:04:46,500
<i>you have to review the steps
and figure out what went wrong.</i>

64
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:51,600
<i>At this point, that’s all
I can think about.</i>

65
00:04:52,700 --> 00:04:54,633
<i> Where did I go wrong?</i>

66
00:04:56,033 --> 00:04:59,633
<i>Let’s go back to the
beginning of the end.</i>

67
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:09,367
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

68
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:46,767
Is this what turns you on?

69
00:05:47,333 --> 00:05:48,633
Blindfolds, really?

70
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:51,733
Here I come...

71
00:05:51,733 --> 00:05:52,800
You're really one of a kind.

72
00:05:53,533 --> 00:05:54,633
Where are you?

73
00:05:54,967 --> 00:05:56,567
Coming...

74
00:05:57,433 --> 00:05:59,633
Make sure I'll be surprised.

75
00:05:59,833 --> 00:06:00,767
[CHUCKLES]

76
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:04,833
Ta-da!

77
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:07,533
Wow...

78
00:06:09,033 --> 00:06:10,833
You're so beautiful, Marla.

79
00:06:13,667 --> 00:06:14,733
I want you to know...

80
00:06:16,067 --> 00:06:18,767
I’m the luckiest man
in the world.

81
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,567
I've been waiting for this,
Marla.

82
00:06:22,133 --> 00:06:23,833
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

83
00:06:28,367 --> 00:06:30,833
Oh... Wow!

84
00:06:32,667 --> 00:06:33,933
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

85
00:06:36,567 --> 00:06:38,500
Touch me gently...

86
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:45,467
Oh, are you okay?

87
00:06:48,067 --> 00:06:49,367
Yeah...

88
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:50,800
For real?

89
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:52,700
Of course!

90
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:55,433
- Really?
- Yes! I’m so sure!

91
00:06:55,433 --> 00:06:56,933
See, I'm so ready!

92
00:06:57,133 --> 00:06:59,100
How can you be ready when you’re
several feet away from me?

93
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:01,067
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

94
00:07:01,067 --> 00:07:02,700
Marla, we're so far apart.

95
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:04,400
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

96
00:07:04,633 --> 00:07:05,667
Ah...

97
00:07:05,933 --> 00:07:07,667
this is just...

98
00:07:07,667 --> 00:07:09,700
you know, inertia.

99
00:07:10,733 --> 00:07:11,667
I’m just...

100
00:07:11,867 --> 00:07:13,067
really nervous.

101
00:07:13,533 --> 00:07:15,700
Marla, if you're not ready,
it's okay.

102
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:17,533
No!

103
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:19,867
I’m ready!
I’m ready, I promise!

104
00:07:20,067 --> 00:07:21,000
I just need to...

105
00:07:21,467 --> 00:07:22,700
I just need to warm up.

106
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:24,167
Whoo! Okay!

107
00:07:24,733 --> 00:07:25,733
I’m alive!

108
00:07:25,733 --> 00:07:26,767
I’m alert!

109
00:07:26,767 --> 00:07:27,800
I’m enthusiastic!

110
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:29,667
Okay.

111
00:07:29,667 --> 00:07:30,733
Give it to me.

112
00:07:31,767 --> 00:07:32,767
You're so adorable.

113
00:07:33,133 --> 00:07:35,867
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

114
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:45,800
[DREAMY MUSIC PLAYING]

115
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:08,833
[GIGGLES]

116
00:08:11,033 --> 00:08:13,033
I’m ticklish.

117
00:08:16,133 --> 00:08:17,867
That tickles!

118
00:08:19,067 --> 00:08:20,100
[GASPS]

119
00:08:20,867 --> 00:08:24,867
[RAPID HEARTBEAT]

120
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:31,500
That tickled...

121
00:08:38,667 --> 00:08:40,533
I'm not forcing you, am I?

122
00:08:41,233 --> 00:08:42,700
If you're not ready,

123
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:45,000
you shouldn’t have gotten
my hopes up.

124
00:08:49,567 --> 00:08:50,833
I'm sorry...

125
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:53,000
It’s not you...

126
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:55,567
it’s me?

127
00:08:55,767 --> 00:08:58,733
Did the top of our batch
just use

128
00:08:58,933 --> 00:09:00,633
“it’s not you, it’s me” on me?

129
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:03,867
It’s just...

130
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:08,500
I really imagined my
first time would be like...

131
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:11,700
how I would whip up
a synthesis of aspirin.

132
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:12,667
Huh?

133
00:09:14,267 --> 00:09:16,633
Really? Synthesis of aspirin?

134
00:09:16,633 --> 00:09:19,133
I was just hoping
that it would be...

135
00:09:20,133 --> 00:09:21,200
special.

136
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:23,000
Magical.

137
00:09:24,967 --> 00:09:25,900
You know...

138
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:27,800
I get you, Marla.

139
00:09:28,033 --> 00:09:29,867
- Okay?
- Really?

140
00:09:35,267 --> 00:09:36,600
I love you.

141
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,333
There are certain equations

142
00:09:40,333 --> 00:09:41,967
that are hard to crack.

143
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:44,233
Do you know...

144
00:09:45,633 --> 00:09:47,200
the Collatz Conjecture?

145
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:50,233
[WHIRRING]

146
00:09:50,233 --> 00:09:51,200
Yes.

147
00:09:51,867 --> 00:09:53,867
While deceptively
simple to state,

148
00:09:53,867 --> 00:09:55,933
the Collatz Conjecture
hasn’t been solved

149
00:09:55,933 --> 00:09:58,200
in over half a century.

150
00:09:58,767 --> 00:09:59,833
Exactly.

151
00:10:00,633 --> 00:10:02,900
That's why I'm trying
to solve it,

152
00:10:03,867 --> 00:10:07,867
even if it takes me
another half a century.

153
00:10:07,867 --> 00:10:10,133
[DREAMY MUSIC RESUMES]

154
00:10:10,133 --> 00:10:11,700
That’s how much I love you.

155
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,933
I'm willing to wait for you.

156
00:10:13,933 --> 00:10:14,900
Aww!

157
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:16,933
You know, that’s
the most beautiful thing

158
00:10:16,933 --> 00:10:18,567
you’ve ever said to me.

159
00:10:19,233 --> 00:10:20,167
[KISSES]

160
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,567
What do you want to do now?

161
00:10:26,133 --> 00:10:27,867
I need to...

162
00:10:28,233 --> 00:10:29,633
I need to...

163
00:10:29,633 --> 00:10:31,233
- [LAUGHS]
- [SCREAMS]

164
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:32,833
Stop!

165
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:40,967
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYS]

166
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:45,733
Can we be groupmates
for the science fair?

167
00:10:47,167 --> 00:10:49,967
Um, that depends
on our ranks, right?

168
00:10:51,267 --> 00:10:52,300
Marla,

169
00:10:52,700 --> 00:10:54,167
where's your confidence in us?

170
00:10:54,367 --> 00:10:56,367
We'll certainly be groupmates

171
00:10:56,367 --> 00:10:58,200
because we’re the smartest
in our batch.

172
00:10:58,733 --> 00:11:00,233
But again, that depends.

173
00:11:00,233 --> 00:11:02,333
Although Cole and I are
talking about it.

174
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:03,900
Speaking of Cole...

175
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:06,367
So what happened last weekend?

176
00:11:08,033 --> 00:11:09,033
Um...

177
00:11:09,033 --> 00:11:10,233
Nothing much...

178
00:11:10,233 --> 00:11:12,733
We just researched about JWST.

179
00:11:12,733 --> 00:11:14,000
JWST?

180
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:16,733
Daphne?

181
00:11:17,267 --> 00:11:18,933
JWST.

182
00:11:19,133 --> 00:11:20,867
James Webb Space Telescope.

183
00:11:20,867 --> 00:11:21,833
My goodness.

184
00:11:21,833 --> 00:11:22,933
[SCOFFS]

185
00:11:22,933 --> 00:11:24,167
Girl...

186
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:27,033
I know what the
James Webb Space Telescope is.

187
00:11:27,033 --> 00:11:29,167
What I’m pointing at is...

188
00:11:29,433 --> 00:11:31,300
what happened between
you and Cole last weekend?

189
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:33,100
I wanna know the details!

190
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:37,133
- [STALL DOOR OPENS]
- [TOILET FLUSHES]

191
00:11:37,133 --> 00:11:38,667
[STALL DOOR SLAMS]

192
00:11:38,667 --> 00:11:43,133
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [WATER TURNS ON]

193
00:11:43,167 --> 00:11:46,333
Sorry, Isobel, we didn't know
you were in there.

194
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:49,800
Yeah. You're peeing so quietly.

195
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:51,300
Are you on silent mode?

196
00:11:53,067 --> 00:11:54,667
Funny.

197
00:11:55,733 --> 00:11:59,033
Just take your time, and make
sure your hands are clean.

198
00:11:59,033 --> 00:12:00,467
Do you need some hand alcohol?

199
00:12:00,467 --> 00:12:01,800
I have some.

200
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:03,700
Your hands must be so dirty,
right?

201
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:05,233
Hm! Daphne...

202
00:12:05,233 --> 00:12:07,933
You know what, Dessalyn

203
00:12:07,933 --> 00:12:09,433
[SCOFFS]

204
00:12:09,433 --> 00:12:10,933
It's Daphne.

205
00:12:10,933 --> 00:12:12,267
Dessalyn.

206
00:12:12,267 --> 00:12:13,933
That's your real name, right?

207
00:12:13,933 --> 00:12:16,000
Because you're so fake
and pretentious.

208
00:12:16,033 --> 00:12:16,900
[CHUCKLES]

209
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:20,367
Daphne is a far cry
from Dessalyn.

210
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,767
Maybe it's you who needs
to clean your name.

211
00:12:24,767 --> 00:12:25,767
It stinks!

212
00:12:25,767 --> 00:12:27,233
What if I beat your face in?!

213
00:12:27,233 --> 00:12:30,200
Daphne!
We're in school, Daphne.

214
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,167
I'd like to see you try.

215
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:32,767
Would you like a black eye?
[CLAPS] Huh?

216
00:12:33,967 --> 00:12:35,833
- Daphne! Stop.
- Let's square up.

217
00:12:35,833 --> 00:12:36,967
- Daphne! Stop!
- What?!

218
00:12:36,967 --> 00:12:39,300
Watch whose toes you step on.

219
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:40,467
Okay, let's calm down.

220
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:43,200
We're not trying
to pick a fight.

221
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:45,100
Just go.

222
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:47,400
We're lovers, not fighters.

223
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:48,900
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

224
00:12:49,933 --> 00:12:51,167
[DOOR OPENS]

225
00:12:53,167 --> 00:12:54,367
[SCOFFS]

226
00:12:54,367 --> 00:12:57,233
I'd love to poke her eyes out!

227
00:12:57,233 --> 00:12:59,300
She's so annoying!

228
00:12:59,300 --> 00:13:01,300
Oh my god, yes, but...

229
00:13:02,333 --> 00:13:04,367
Just-- you know...
Just don't mind her.

230
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:06,400
Isobel's just like that.

231
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:08,333
She's just...

232
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:09,867
really weird.

233
00:13:11,067 --> 00:13:13,100
[MUSIC FADES]

234
00:13:25,467 --> 00:13:27,367
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

235
00:13:27,367 --> 00:13:29,200
- [ANT] What's up?
- Yo!

236
00:13:31,033 --> 00:13:32,467
What's that?

237
00:13:32,467 --> 00:13:34,300
The one you sent us.

238
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:35,200
Wow.

239
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:37,333
You're enjoying it
way too much, bro!

240
00:13:37,333 --> 00:13:38,967
You fool.

241
00:13:38,967 --> 00:13:40,567
Who wouldn't be surprised
by what you've just sent?

242
00:13:40,567 --> 00:13:43,933
Just in case you're forgetting,
that's still my girlfriend.

243
00:13:43,933 --> 00:13:45,067
- I know!
- Huh?

244
00:13:45,067 --> 00:13:47,233
- Like I always tell you...
- What?

245
00:13:47,233 --> 00:13:49,000
I think you can do better.

246
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:49,967
- Bro! Loosen up!
- What?!

247
00:13:49,967 --> 00:13:51,367
It's too tight! It's too tight!

248
00:13:51,367 --> 00:13:53,400
You're annoying!

249
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:55,500
I've told you a million times,

250
00:13:55,533 --> 00:13:58,367
Nyx is one of a kind.

251
00:13:58,367 --> 00:14:01,467
I'm not like you who
always ogles at other women!

252
00:14:01,467 --> 00:14:03,000
Hey!

253
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,500
Let me tell you something, okay?

254
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:06,233
Number one,

255
00:14:06,233 --> 00:14:08,300
I am loyal to Daphne.

256
00:14:08,300 --> 00:14:09,933
- Loyal?
- Loyal.

257
00:14:09,933 --> 00:14:11,133
Number two,

258
00:14:11,133 --> 00:14:13,900
there is nothing wrong
with looking.

259
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:15,333
You're looking at
my girlfriend too, right?

260
00:14:15,333 --> 00:14:16,500
- Of course!
- See?

261
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:18,467
But I'm just saying,

262
00:14:18,467 --> 00:14:21,200
I have the best girlfriend, bro!

263
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,933
- [CHUCKLES]
- Besides...

264
00:14:22,933 --> 00:14:25,967
what can I do
if my girlfriend's obsessed

265
00:14:25,967 --> 00:14:27,133
with my muscles, right?

266
00:14:27,133 --> 00:14:28,467
- See this?
- Stop.

267
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:31,500
Yo! Stop flexing your muscles

268
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:33,033
Do you see these, though?

269
00:14:34,267 --> 00:14:36,033
