534
00:27:49,067 --> 00:27:50,933
- Hey.
- What's up, man? Hey?

535
00:27:51,667 --> 00:27:53,700
- You look good.
- It's Earl.

536
00:27:54,300 --> 00:27:56,167
Huh? Who's Earl?

537
00:27:56,167 --> 00:27:58,300
Me. My name is Earl.

538
00:27:58,300 --> 00:28:02,200
Since when? [CHUCKLES]

539
00:28:03,133 --> 00:28:04,300
Anyway...

540
00:28:06,100 --> 00:28:09,800
Where's the homework
I asked you to do?

541
00:28:10,733 --> 00:28:12,033
Come on, let's go.

542
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:15,867
Alright!

543
00:28:16,433 --> 00:28:18,833
If you keep this up, Pearl...

544
00:28:19,900 --> 00:28:22,000
- we might just get along.
- It's Earl, without a P--

545
00:28:22,933 --> 00:28:25,000
[LESTER] What?! Huh?!

546
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:27,467
Let me make it clear
to you, Pearl.

547
00:28:27,467 --> 00:28:29,733
I can call you whatever I want.

548
00:28:29,733 --> 00:28:30,767
Les...

549
00:28:30,767 --> 00:28:32,267
- Les--
- Am I clear?!

550
00:28:32,267 --> 00:28:33,833
- Lester.
- [DAPHNE] Les!

551
00:28:33,833 --> 00:28:34,833
Dumbass!

552
00:28:34,833 --> 00:28:36,900
[MOCKS A STAMMER]

553
00:28:36,900 --> 00:28:40,767
[LAUGHS]

554
00:28:43,867 --> 00:28:45,400
Good morning, class.

555
00:28:48,700 --> 00:28:50,800
[CLEARS THROAT]

556
00:28:53,700 --> 00:28:55,900
Chin up. Smile.

557
00:28:57,467 --> 00:28:59,200
[LESTER SCOFFS,
CLEARS THROAT]

558
00:29:00,433 --> 00:29:02,467
- [LESTER GROANS]
- [TEACHER] Alright.

559
00:29:02,467 --> 00:29:04,100
First things first.

560
00:29:04,933 --> 00:29:06,867
Your grades
for the first quarter

561
00:29:06,867 --> 00:29:08,433
will be released today,

562
00:29:08,433 --> 00:29:11,467
as well as the results
of your quarterly exams.

563
00:29:11,467 --> 00:29:14,267
Now, obviously,
we're still in the top 20.

564
00:29:14,267 --> 00:29:16,767
So, give yourselves
a round of applause.

565
00:29:16,767 --> 00:29:20,100
[APPLAUSE]

566
00:29:20,100 --> 00:29:22,500
[TEACHER] Yes, that is one hell
of an achievement,

567
00:29:22,500 --> 00:29:24,833
especially for our school.

568
00:29:24,833 --> 00:29:27,133
However, while we are
still in the Top 20,

569
00:29:27,133 --> 00:29:28,333
there are some...

570
00:29:29,233 --> 00:29:32,333
changes in the rankings.

571
00:29:32,333 --> 00:29:35,167
Ms. Briones, you have
nothing to worry about,

572
00:29:35,167 --> 00:29:37,867
because you are still top one.

573
00:29:37,867 --> 00:29:43,267
[APPLAUSE]

574
00:29:43,267 --> 00:29:44,467
[TEACHER]
Now, if you keep that up,

575
00:29:44,467 --> 00:29:47,833
we may already have
our valedictorian.

576
00:29:47,833 --> 00:29:49,533
But it's still
too early to tell.

577
00:29:49,533 --> 00:29:51,133
Well, I guess, we shall see.

578
00:29:51,133 --> 00:29:55,067
Projected on the screen
are your grades

579
00:29:55,067 --> 00:29:56,533
for this quarter.

580
00:29:56,533 --> 00:30:00,033
Coming in at second place
is Ms. Calaquian.

581
00:30:00,033 --> 00:30:04,167
[APPLAUSE]

582
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:07,333
She is followed by Ms. Baldemor.

583
00:30:07,333 --> 00:30:09,533
- Fourth, Ms. Rodriguez.
- [SQUEALS]

584
00:30:09,533 --> 00:30:11,533
Nug-nug, I'm number four!

585
00:30:11,533 --> 00:30:13,933
Are you proud of me?
Are you proud of me?

586
00:30:13,933 --> 00:30:15,367
Of course, you're proud of me.

587
00:30:15,367 --> 00:30:17,033
I'm number four, nug-nug!

588
00:30:17,033 --> 00:30:18,800
Congrats, nug-nug.

589
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:19,900
Okay.

590
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:24,500
And finishing with
top 5 is Mr. Javier.

591
00:30:24,500 --> 00:30:26,167
[APPLAUSE]

592
00:30:26,167 --> 00:30:27,167
- [STUDENT 1] Cole!
- [STUDENT 2] Congrats!

593
00:30:27,167 --> 00:30:30,100
Now the rest of you can check
your grades

594
00:30:30,100 --> 00:30:32,833
on your personal
online bulletins.

595
00:30:32,833 --> 00:30:33,800
Alright?

596
00:30:36,267 --> 00:30:37,267
Now...

597
00:30:37,267 --> 00:30:39,200
Uh... Sir.

598
00:30:40,567 --> 00:30:41,967
May I speak?

599
00:30:44,300 --> 00:30:45,900
Um...

600
00:30:46,500 --> 00:30:48,167
Sure, but make it quick.

601
00:30:48,167 --> 00:30:49,567
- We have a class.
- Yes, sir. Thank you.

602
00:30:55,500 --> 00:30:57,533
I just wanted to say...

603
00:30:58,967 --> 00:31:01,600
that ranks are just
numbers, right?

604
00:31:01,600 --> 00:31:05,067
What matters is that
we did our best.

605
00:31:05,067 --> 00:31:07,600
And, hello? We're still
the cream of the crop!

606
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:10,400
And that's something that
should be celebrated.

607
00:31:10,433 --> 00:31:13,400
Which is why I would like
to give a shout out

608
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:15,967
to someone very special...

609
00:31:15,967 --> 00:31:17,133
Cole.

610
00:31:17,967 --> 00:31:22,300
Thank you so much for always
believing in me,

611
00:31:22,300 --> 00:31:24,633
for empowering me,

612
00:31:24,633 --> 00:31:28,600
and for helping me be the best
version of myself.

613
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:33,233
Everyone, please give him
a round of applause.

614
00:31:33,233 --> 00:31:40,200
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

615
00:31:51,900 --> 00:31:53,000
Cole?

616
00:31:56,667 --> 00:31:58,200
Cole?

617
00:31:58,200 --> 00:32:05,133
[INDISTINCT OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

618
00:32:06,233 --> 00:32:13,167
[MUSIC BECOMES DARK]

619
00:32:14,433 --> 00:32:16,200
[THUD]

620
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:20,333
[ISOBEL EXHALES SHARPLY]

621
00:32:22,433 --> 00:32:24,167
You like it rough.

622
00:32:24,167 --> 00:32:25,500
Just the way I like it.

623
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:28,900
Isobel, please,
I'm not in the mood.

624
00:32:29,467 --> 00:32:30,533
Because?

625
00:32:33,633 --> 00:32:35,467
Do I need to give a reason?

626
00:32:36,300 --> 00:32:38,000
I'm just not in the mood.

627
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:38,933
[SLAMS LOCKER]

628
00:32:40,133 --> 00:32:42,533
I'm insulted by your rejection.

629
00:32:42,533 --> 00:32:43,567
Do you want me
to remind you

630
00:32:43,567 --> 00:32:45,633
how you begged for me
to give you a chance?

631
00:32:45,633 --> 00:32:47,333
Do you want to beg again?

632
00:32:52,433 --> 00:32:53,467
What's wrong?

633
00:32:54,500 --> 00:32:55,567
Tell me.

634
00:32:56,667 --> 00:32:58,067
Now!

635
00:32:58,067 --> 00:32:59,667
I was surprised you
ranked second.

636
00:33:01,133 --> 00:33:02,167
Me too!

637
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:05,000
Finally...

638
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:08,133
Finally someone agrees
with me.

639
00:33:08,967 --> 00:33:10,967
I thought I was going to be
number one this time,

640
00:33:10,967 --> 00:33:13,333
but that girlfriend of yours
is just lucky

641
00:33:13,333 --> 00:33:15,367
that she has
a photographic memory.

642
00:33:15,367 --> 00:33:18,000
But did she actually understand
what she was reading?

643
00:33:19,233 --> 00:33:20,333
But wait...

644
00:33:21,500 --> 00:33:23,933
What does my rank
have to do with this?

645
00:33:27,700 --> 00:33:29,167
Are you jealous?

646
00:33:29,167 --> 00:33:30,033
[SCOFFS]

647
00:33:30,033 --> 00:33:32,133
Then you should've
studied harder.

648
00:33:32,733 --> 00:33:34,633
Or you should've hired
a tutor.

649
00:33:35,633 --> 00:33:36,600
[THUD]

650
00:33:36,600 --> 00:33:41,067
[COLE BREATHING HEAVILY]

651
00:33:41,067 --> 00:33:42,333
You're angry...

652
00:33:43,367 --> 00:33:46,233
because two of your girlfriends
outsmarted you.

653
00:33:49,233 --> 00:33:50,700
Did I hurt your ego?

654
00:33:50,700 --> 00:33:54,400
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

655
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:55,533
Isobel...

656
00:33:56,267 --> 00:33:59,533
I don't owe you
or anyone an explanation.

657
00:34:01,300 --> 00:34:03,367
I don't give a damn
about your ranking.

658
00:34:04,767 --> 00:34:07,600
Because even if you turn
the world upside down...

659
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:15,133
you'll never be
my number one.

660
00:34:15,133 --> 00:34:16,167
- [COLE GRUNTS]
- [SLAMS LOCKER]

661
00:34:16,167 --> 00:34:18,667
[COLE BREATHING HEAVILY]

662
00:34:18,667 --> 00:34:22,033
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

663
00:34:22,033 --> 00:34:23,533
You're never going to break up
with Marla...

664
00:34:24,533 --> 00:34:25,600
won't you?

665
00:34:26,433 --> 00:34:27,433
Maybe I could.

666
00:34:27,433 --> 00:34:33,767
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

667
00:34:33,800 --> 00:34:35,333
Is that what you want?

668
00:34:37,767 --> 00:34:39,600
You want this?

669
00:34:42,700 --> 00:34:46,467
Only if you beat Marla
and rank first.

670
00:34:48,300 --> 00:34:50,567
- Watch me.
- Okay.

671
00:34:52,100 --> 00:34:53,300
Let's see if you can do it.

672
00:34:58,200 --> 00:34:59,400
I can.

673
00:35:07,567 --> 00:35:09,367
Call me when you're
done moping.

674
00:35:10,733 --> 00:35:14,200
This sad boy energy
doesn't suit you.

675
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:15,600
- You look pathetic!
- [THUD]

676
00:35:18,233 --> 00:35:19,333
[SMOOCHES]

677
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:23,100
Number five.

678
00:35:24,800 --> 00:35:26,300
- [GRUNTS]
- [THUD]

679
00:35:27,267 --> 00:35:28,433
- [GRUNTS]
- [THUD]

680
00:35:28,433 --> 00:35:33,433
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

681
00:35:33,433 --> 00:35:40,367
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

682
00:35:46,433 --> 00:35:48,433
[MUSIC FADES]

683
00:35:48,433 --> 00:35:52,867
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

684
00:35:52,867 --> 00:35:54,167
Hey.

685
00:35:57,267 --> 00:35:58,767
[MARLA] I've been looking
for you.

686
00:36:00,133 --> 00:36:01,367
Can we talk?

687
00:36:08,700 --> 00:36:09,867
Hey, guys.

688
00:36:10,933 --> 00:36:12,233
Leave!

689
00:36:13,167 --> 00:36:14,400
Let's go!

690
00:36:14,800 --> 00:36:17,433
Come on, come on, come on!
Let's go! Let's go!

691
00:36:18,467 --> 00:36:20,167
Thanks, guys. Study well.

692
00:36:28,933 --> 00:36:31,800
- [MARLA] Are you mad?
- What do you think?

693
00:36:35,633 --> 00:36:37,467
I begged you, remember?

694
00:36:38,833 --> 00:36:41,633
Marla, this is the first time
I asked a favor from you, right?

695
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:45,533
Is it hard to make
a few mistakes on our exams?

696
00:36:46,633 --> 00:36:49,533
It's not as if I asked you
to get a failing grade.

697
00:36:49,533 --> 00:36:52,900
I was just asking for
a little consideration,

698
00:36:52,900 --> 00:36:55,633
so I could be the top in our
class even just this quarter.

699
00:36:55,633 --> 00:36:58,233
Just one quarter! So that my dad
won't get mad at me!

700
00:36:58,233 --> 00:36:59,867
You know how he's like, right?

701
00:37:02,500 --> 00:37:03,833
- But...
- What?

702
00:37:08,967 --> 00:37:10,833
Cole, it's just that...

703
00:37:12,200 --> 00:37:16,167
even if I got some of the
answers wrong,

704
00:37:17,300 --> 00:37:19,900
you still wouldn't be
the top in our class.

705
00:37:20,867 --> 00:37:23,300
So, you're saying
that I'm dumb?

706
00:37:24,333 --> 00:37:26,333
- No. No.
- Is that what you're implying?

707
00:37:26,333 --> 00:37:28,233
- No. It's not that.
- Is that it?

708
00:37:28,233 --> 00:37:29,600
Then what?!

709
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:32,567
Hey. Hey.

710
00:37:32,567 --> 00:37:35,333
You're a SOSH student.

711
00:37:35,333 --> 00:37:37,433
No one here is dumb.

712
00:37:37,433 --> 00:37:40,367
And no one is calling
you that.

713
00:37:40,367 --> 00:37:43,700
But I admit I was scared
to give up my rank

714
00:37:43,700 --> 00:37:45,633
because I have goals, too.

715
00:37:46,333 --> 00:37:49,833
I want to graduate on top and
get a scholarship in Harvard.

716
00:37:51,367 --> 00:37:53,600
We all have dreams, don't we?

717
00:37:53,600 --> 00:37:56,667
Yes, we have dreams.

718
00:37:56,667 --> 00:37:59,800
But why did you agree
to give way for me, Marla?

719
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:01,967
Why did you give me
false hopes?

720
00:38:01,967 --> 00:38:03,900
Do you know what
would happen to me

721
00:38:03,900 --> 00:38:06,500
if Daddy finds out that
the top four students

722
00:38:06,500 --> 00:38:08,367
in our batch
are all women?

723
00:38:08,367 --> 00:38:09,767
There's nothing wrong with that.

724
00:38:09,767 --> 00:38:11,633
You don't understand, Marla,

725
00:38:11,633 --> 00:38:14,033
because you already got
what you want.

726
00:38:14,033 --> 00:38:15,733
I thought you loved me.

727
00:38:16,867 --> 00:38:17,867
I do.

728
00:38:17,867 --> 00:38:20,800
But your grades
are more important to you.

729
00:38:22,400 --> 00:38:23,367
No.

730
00:38:24,633 --> 00:38:27,600
Cole, I love you.

731
00:38:27,600 --> 00:38:30,500
But you couldn't give way
for me.

732
00:38:30,500 --> 00:38:32,933
You know I'm applying for
an internship at NASA, right?

733
00:38:32,933 --> 00:38:34,633
My future depends on that!

734
00:38:35,833 --> 00:38:38,633
You know that they'll only get
the top student

735
00:38:38,633 --> 00:38:41,867
from each country and you
made my chances even lower!

736
00:38:42,767 --> 00:38:45,533
What's the point
of this relationship, Marla?

737
00:38:45,533 --> 00:38:47,567
If this is just how it is
for you,

738
00:38:47,567 --> 00:38:50,933
we should rethink
about this relationship,

739
00:38:50,933 --> 00:38:54,267
and if we even have
a future together.

740
00:38:57,400 --> 00:38:59,067
[COLE EXHALES LOUDLY]

741
00:38:59,067 --> 00:39:00,967
Cole, please.

742
00:39:00,967 --> 00:39:04,333
Don't ambush me with a threat
of a breakup, please.

743
00:39:04,333 --> 00:39:05,867
It's not a threat, Marla.

744
00:39:05,867 --> 00:39:07,400
It feels like it.

745
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:09,000
So, what do you want me
to do?

746
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:11,600
Should I just blame myself?

747
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:13,633
Am I the one
at fault here, Marla?

748
00:39:13,633 --> 00:39:16,333
When I get home,
Daddy would kill me.

749
00:39:16,333 --> 00:39:18,700
I don't know how
you could make it up to me,

750
00:39:18,700 --> 00:39:20,767
but please, Marla...

751
00:39:20,767 --> 00:39:23,667
Please leave me alone.

752
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:30,500
Do you still love me?

753
00:39:34,067 --> 00:39:35,733
Collatz Conjecture.

754
00:39:36,600 --> 00:39:43,600
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

755
00:39:50,467 --> 00:39:57,467
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

756
00:39:58,833 --> 00:40:02,767
[WOMAN RETCHES, COUGHS]

757
00:40:04,567 --> 00:40:07,033
[WOMAN GROANS]

758
00:40:07,033 --> 00:40:08,667
[WOMAN RETCHES]

759
00:40:08,667 --> 00:40:09,633
Mommy?

760
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:12,400
Mommy, what happened?

761
00:40:12,400 --> 00:40:14,433
Why is Mommy throwing up?

762
00:40:14,433 --> 00:40:16,567
She was drinking when I picked
her up from the restaurant.

763
00:40:17,733 --> 00:40:18,933
Mommy...

764
00:40:18,933 --> 00:40:21,000
It's only eight in the evening
and you're already drunk.

765
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:24,000
They're all leaving me!

766
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:25,100
Who left you?

767
00:40:25,100 --> 00:40:26,800
Henry!

768
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:28,033
Henry?

769
00:40:28,833 --> 00:40:31,633
Ah Your boyfriend?

770
00:40:31,633 --> 00:40:33,100
He just left me,

771
00:40:33,100 --> 00:40:35,600
just like what your father
did to me.

772
00:40:35,600 --> 00:40:36,733
Just like Blake...

773
00:40:36,767 --> 00:40:38,467
Just like Anthony...

774
00:40:39,433 --> 00:40:41,600
They're all the same.

775
00:40:41,600 --> 00:40:44,567
People always abandon me!

776
00:40:44,567 --> 00:40:46,667
Mom, that's not true.

777
00:40:46,667 --> 00:40:48,733
I'm here for you.
I'm still here.

778
00:40:50,600 --> 00:40:52,167
But you hate me.

779
00:40:52,167 --> 00:40:53,633
[LAUGHS]

780
00:40:53,633 --> 00:40:57,200
- No, of course not.
- Yes, you do.

781
00:40:57,200 --> 00:41:00,767
You blame me for why
your father left us.

782
00:41:00,767 --> 00:41:02,800
You just blame me
for everything.

783
00:41:03,767 --> 00:41:07,833
It's not your fault that Dad
chose to go with his mistress.

784
00:41:07,833 --> 00:41:09,800
And I never blamed you
for that.

785
00:41:10,933 --> 00:41:14,200
Also, Mommy, why are you
doing this to yourself?

786
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:17,200
It's not even a month since
you've been dating...

787
00:41:17,200 --> 00:41:19,133
What's his name again? Henry?

788
00:41:19,133 --> 00:41:20,767
It's not even a month.

789
00:41:20,767 --> 00:41:22,767
You weren't that devastated
when Dad left.

790
00:41:22,767 --> 00:41:23,833
[SCOFFS]

791
00:41:23,833 --> 00:41:27,667
It's not about how
long a relationship lasted.

792
00:41:27,667 --> 00:41:30,533
You see...

793
00:41:30,533 --> 00:41:33,567
You don't know anything
about relationships.

794
00:41:33,567 --> 00:41:37,600
Do you even know how to
make a relationship work?

795
00:41:37,600 --> 00:41:39,467
Are you even willing to...

796
